      "answer_id": 74771849,
      "question_id": 74770488,
      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<h1>Dirctory</h1>\n<pre><code>.\n├── Dockerfile\n├── hamcrest-core-1.1.jar\n├── json-simple-1.1.1.jar\n└── ProcInputJson-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar\n</code></pre>\n<h1>Dockerfile</h1>\n<pre><code>FROM eclipse-temurin:17.0.5_8-jre-ubi9-minimal\nWORKDIR /data\nCOPY ProcInputJson-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar /app.jar\nCOPY hamcrest-core-1.1.jar /hamcrest-core-1.1.jar\nCOPY json-simple-1.1.1.jar /json-simple-1.1.1.jar\nENTRYPOINT [&quot;java&quot;,&quot;-jar&quot;, &quot;/app.jar&quot;]\n</code></pre>\n<h1>Build Command</h1>\n<pre><code>export VERSION=1.0.0\nexport DOCKER_NAME=proc-input-json\n\ndocker build -t ${DOCKER_NAME}:${VERSION} .\n       \ndocker tag ${DOCKER_NAME}:${VERSION} ${DOCKER_NAME}:latest\n</code></pre>\n<h1>Test Command</h1>\n<p><strong>In a any directory</strong></p>\n<pre><code>.\n└── data\n    ├── 1.json\n    └── 2.json\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Run Command</strong></p>\n<pre><code>docker run -it -v `pwd`/data:/data proc-input-json 1.json 2.json\n</code></pre>\n"
    }
